Source: loopjefe-lv2
Section: sound
Priority: optional
Maintainer: pistomp <pistomp@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), lv2-dev
Standards-Version: 4.6.2

Package: loopjefe-lv2
Architecture: arm64
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: LoopJefe beat-synced multitrack looper LV2 plugin (pi-Stomp fork)
 Fork of mod-audio/sooperlooper-lv2-plugin (itself derived from Jesse
 Chappell's SooperLooper LADSPA plugin), adding bar-quantized recording
 driven by the LV2 time extension and a single-CC 4-state cycle (Empty ->
 Recording -> Playback <-> Stopped, plus state/reset control ports) for
 the pi-Stomp multitrack looper workflow. Ships both the mono (loopjefe)
 and stereo (loopjefe-2x2) bundles.
